05073nam a22008295i 9780520972599DE-B159720210621102733.0m|||||o||d||||||||cr || ||||||||210621t20192019cau    fo  d z      eng d  a2018059589  a97805209725997 a10.1525/97805209725992doi  a(DE-B1597)537391  a(OCoLC)1079412290  aDE-B1597bengcDE-B1597erda0 aeng  acaucUS-CA10aBR65.E636 4aBR65.E636 7aREL1140002bisacsh04a264/.0140232231 aWickes, Jeffrey, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut10aBible and Poetry in Late Antique Mesopotamia :bEphrem's Hymns on Faith /cJeffrey Wickes. 1aBerkeley, CA : bUniversity of California Press, c[2019] 4cÂ©2019  a1 online resource (226 p.)  atextbtxt2rdacontent  acomputerbc2rdamedia  aonline resourcebcr2rdacarrier  atext filebPDF2rda0 aChristianity in Late Antiquity ;v500tFrontmatter -- tContents -- tAbbreviations -- tAcknowledgments -- tNote to the Reader -- tIntroduction -- tPART ONE. Ephrem and the Late Antique World -- t1. Ephrem's Madrashe on Faith in Context -- t2. Investigation -- tPART TWO. The Biblical Poetics of the Madrashe on Faith -- t3. Bible, Polemics, and Language -- t4. The Poet's "I" -- t5. Audience and the Vision of the Text -- t6. A Divine Son -- tConclusion -- tNotes -- tBibliography -- tIndex of Bible References -- tGeneral Index0 arestricted accessuhttp://purl.org/coar/access_right/c_16ecfonline access with authorization2star  aEphrem the Syrian was one of the founding voices in Syriac literature. While he wrote in a variety of genres, the bulk of his work took the form of madrashe, a Syriac genre of musical poetry or hymns. In Bible and Poetry in Late Antique Mesopotamia, Jeffrey Wickes offers a thoroughly contextualized study of Ephrem's magnum opus, the Hymns on Faith, delivered in response to the theological controversies that followed the First Council of Nicaea. The ensuing doctrinal divisions had tremendous impact on the course of Christianity and led in part to the development of a uniquely Syriac Church, in which Ephrem would become a central figure. Drawing on literary, ritual, and performance theories, Bible and Poetry shows how Ephrem used the Syriac Bible to construct and conceive of himself and his audience. In so doing, Wickes resituates Ephrem in a broader early Christian context and contributes to discussions of literature and religion in late antiquity.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 21. Jun 2021) 0aHymns, SyriacxHistory and criticism. 7aRELIGION / Ancient.2bisacsh  achristianity.  acollection of syriac poetry.  acontextualized.  aearly christian context.  aephrem the syrian.  afounding voices in syriac literature.  afourth century.  ainsightful.  aliterature and religion in late antiquity.  amadrashe.  amusical poetry or hymns.  aspiritual.  asyriac poet.  asyrica literature.  athe hymns of faith study.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2019 Englishz978311061076508iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2019z9783110664232oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Theol., Relig. Stud., Jewish Stud.2019 Englishz978311061074108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Theology, Relig. Studies, Jewish Studies 2019z9783110606508oZDB-23-DGF08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUCA Complete eBook-Package 2019z978311065207908iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Complete eBook-Package 2019z978311066763940uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/9780520972599zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de Gruyter40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520972599423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780520972599.jpg  a978-3-11-061074-1  EBOOK PACKAGE Theol., Relig. Stud., Jewish Stud.2019 Englishb2019  a978-3-11-061